PROBLEM:
When launching an AndroidGameActivity from a notification the static field ScreenReceiver.ScreenLocked stays on true.
The problem is that then the game won't be initalized because of this check in AndroidGameWindow.OnUpdateFrame:

```
            if (!GameView.IsResuming && _game.Platform.IsActive && !ScreenReceiver.ScreenLocked)
            {
                _game.Tick();
            } 
```

SOLUTION:
Reset ScreenReceiver.ScreenLocked in OnDestroy()

ctor of OpenALSoundController crashes on iOS9 device/simulator with 

> System.EntryPointNotFoundException: alcMacOSXMixerOutputRate

Here is the self-contained example:
https://github.com/xamarin/monotouch-samples/tree/master/BouncingGameCompleteiOS

Looks like there is no symbol for _alcMacOSXMixerOutputRate_ on iOS9. Sample works fine on iOS8.

Also have a look at Apple's sample
https://developer.apple.com/library/mac/samplecode/OpenALExample/Listings/Scene_m.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/DTS10003587-Scene_m-DontLinkElementID_10

```
typedef ALvoid  AL_APIENTRY (*alcMacOSXMixerOutputRateProcPtr) (const ALdouble value);
ALvoid  alcMacOSXMixerOutputRateProc(const ALdouble value)
{
    static  alcMacOSXMixerOutputRateProcPtr proc = NULL;

    if (proc == NULL) {
        proc = (alcMacOSXMixerOutputRateProcPtr) alcGetProcAddress(NULL, (const ALCchar*) "alcMacOSXMixerOutputRate");
    }

    if (proc)
        proc(value);

    return;
}
```

I think that we have to check existance of _alcMacOSXMixerOutputRate_ symbol first before invoke alcMacOSXMixerOutputRate function

I believe that this is a crasher https://github.com/mono/MonoGame/blob/develop/MonoGame.Framework/Audio/OpenALSoundController.cs#L95
